olive oil
20 g butter
1 packet ginger paste
1.25 cup water
1 packet jasmine rice
1 bag Asian Stir-Fry Mix
1 packet oyster sauce
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
½ tbs vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
1 bag green beans
1 packet beef strips
1 sachet lemon pepper spice blend
½ packet cornflour
1 bag mint

• In a medium saucepan, heat the butter with a dash of olive oil over medium heat.
• Cook ginger paste until fragrant, 1-2 minutes. Add the water and a generous pinch of salt to the pan and bring to the boil.
• Add jasmine rice, stir, cover with a lid and reduce heat to low.
• Cook for 12 minutes, then remove from heat and keep covered until rice is tender and water is absorbed, 10-15 minutes.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the ginger paste starts to spatter!
TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don't peek!

• Meanwhile, combine oyster sauce, sweet chilli sauce, the vinegar and a splash of water in a small bowl.
• Trim green beans and slice into thirds.
• Pat beef strips dry with paper towel. In a medium bowl, combine beef strips, lemon pepper spice blend, cornflour(see ingredients) and a generous pinch of salt.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. Cook Asian stir-fry mix and green beans until tender, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a plate.
• Return the pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, shake off excess flour and cook beef in batches, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes. Return all beef to the pan.
• Return cooked veggies to the pan, then add the oyster sauce mixture, tossing to combine, 1 minute.

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over a high heat helps it stay tender.

• Divide ginger rice and Thai-style beef and oyster sauce stir-fry between bowls.
• Tear over mint to serve. Enjoy!